# Coding Conventions

## TypeScript / React
- Arrow functions for all components and handlers
- TypeScript strict — no `any`, use Zod for form validation
- `const` over `let` wherever possible
- Async functions always use try/catch with proper error handling
- Component files: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utility files: `camelCase.ts`

## Supabase
- Always RLS on all tables
- Never expose service role key in frontend
- Use typed responses: `supabase.from<MyType>('table')`
- Auth via Supabase Auth only — no custom auth

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes

## Environment Variables
```
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
```
Never commit `.env` to git.
